CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 7, 1959, pg. 39 reads:"Luncheon For Mr. Spaulding - The North Carolina Mutual Insurance Company greeted its president last Friday, when Asa T. Spalding of Durham, N.C., came to Pittsburgh. J.D. Lewis, manager of the Pittsburgh district office, arranged a luncheon in his honor at the Centre Avenue YMCA, with nearly 100 guests in attendance. At the head table are, left to right: J. D. Lewis, the Rev. Amos Brackeen, W.H. Clement, who came from Duham with Mr. Spaulding; Mrs. Daisy E. Lampkin, Mr. Spaulding, Mrs. Robert L. Vann, the Rev. Frank Felder, Mrs. Homer S. Brown and Richard Robinson, a North Carolina Mutual agent. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Head table, from left: J. D. Lewis, Rev. Amos Brackeen, W. H. Clement, Daisy E. Lampkin, Asa T. Spaulding, Jessie Vann, Rev. Frank Felder, Wilhelmina Byrd Brown, and Richard Robinson, seated in Centre Avenue YMCA, another version
